article.headline: McCarville has 20 points and 17 boards in win
article.linkText: McCarville powers Gophers to rout of Ohio State
article.story:
MINNEAPOLIS (AP) -- Janel McCarville and Corrin Von Wald each scored 20 points, leading (No. 17 ESPN/USA Today, No. 18 AP) Minnesota to a 73-50 win over (No. 24 ESPN/USA Today, No. 22 AP) Ohio State on Sunday.

	   McCarville had a career-high 17 rebounds and dominated under
both backboards in her first game back for the Gophers (19-4, 8-4
Big Ten) after sustaining a concussion Feb. 9 at Indiana. Von Wald
made all five of her shots from 3-point range.

	   Lindsay Whalen, held to a season-low five points in a 66-58 loss
to the Buckeyes on Feb. 6 at Columbus, had a subpar game with 14
points, eight below her average.

	   But Ohio State (17-7, 8-5) could not take advantage of Whalen's
struggles. Harassed by Minnesota's man-to-man defense, the Buckeyes
had trouble getting shots off and rarely got a second chance at the
basket.

	   D'Wan Shackleford scored 14 points to lead Ohio State, with
Courtney Coleman adding 12.

	   McCarville's inside game and Von Wald's outside touch helped
Minnesota gain control of the game early. McCarville scored eight
of Minnesota's first 17 points, and Von Wald made a pair of
3-pointers and a driving layup to give Minnesota a 24-15 lead.

	   The Gophers opened the second half with a 16-6 run, taking a
51-32 lead on Von Wald's 3-pointer with 13:10 remaining.
